1.translation-en: OK, I came back to tell you.

4.translation-en: You will meet him over there.

6.translation-en: Wait a while, soon they will all come past.

7.translation-en: Long ago two people went past.

8.translation-en: OK, the two of them came here.

10.full_text: gari nadyagali gulha yundru yalairri garnaani yanhthadhikagali
10.translation-en: Hey when you were looking over there did a man go past?

13.full_text: gawa ngathu inha dumparra/ nhanigurru nhungka bagalani
13.translation-en: Come, I will show you his track. (Come I will show you / this is his track.)

14.full_text: nadya nhanhaguru/ garnaandru wirlidigala barlkaandru nhanha nanduanha
14.translation-en: Look at that man leading that horse with a string.

notes: is this an imperative with an optional subject? appears to have bare verb, but verb isn't sentence-initial

17.full_text: nhaniyi nugaani/ walya barninyi ngathu nunpalangu

19.translation-en: I will not pull that hair.

22.translation-en: Yes I will roll that one.

23.translation-en: This stone will fall in the water.

24.translation-en: This stone will fall down along the steep bank into the water.

26.translation-en: This stone will roll into the water.

27.translation-en: The two of us will catch this goanna.

28.translation-en: Spear this emu with a spear.

29.translation-en: Yes, I am already spearing it.

32.full_text: gudyu ngathu nhanha nunpalangu dratyalangu nganha
32.translation-en: If/when I kick it, (it) may bite me.

33.full_text: nadyarra gulha ngathu ingka ngarnidyanha/ ngutyarra ngathu nhinha nguthianha
33.translation-en: When I see your father I will give him meat.

36.translation-en: OK, I will throw it away.

41.translation-en: Already this tree is growing quickly.

notes: what-from/what-at (maybe also apprehensive use of locative?)
log looks like it has an accusative case marker on it

55.translation-en: I will go to the doctor I think.

56.translation-en: You will go to the doctor, I think.

57.full_text: munkaiyigala nganyi gukaani/ nadyarra bari yundru nganha
57.translation-en: I am having pains in the head. I think you will see me.

59.translation-en: Tomorrow I think I'll have pains.
